text: Chebarkul () is a rural locality (a village) in Lagerevsky Selsoviet, Salavatsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 214 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 23 km from Maloyaz, 6 km from Lagerevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Salavatsky District
title: Chebarkul, Republic of Bashkortostan
